Claims We claim: 1. An isolated Porcine Epidemic Diarrhea Virus (PEDV) encoded by a DNA polynucleotide that is at least 95% identical, at a full length nucleotide level, to SEQ ID: NO: 67, and that includes one or more of the following amino acid features: (a) L or P at position 551 (immediately after DAT) of polyprotein la/lb as determined by reference to SEQ ID NO: 46, or a conservative substitution thereof; (b) P at position 1009 (immediately after NIT) of spike protein, as determined by reference to SEQ ID NO:47, or a conservative substitution thereof; (c) H at position 973 (immediately after PFS) of spike protein, as determined by reference to SEQ ID NO: 47, or a conservative substitution thereof; and (d) a modification of the encoding sequence of ORF3 that leads to early stop of ORF3 translation. 2. The virus of claim 1 that is encoded by a polynucleotide have the sequence set forth in SEQ ID NO: 35, 36 or 37. 3. The virus of claim 1, wherein said DNA polynucleotide encoding said virus is at least 98% identical, at a full length nucleotide level, to SEQ ID NO:67. 4. The virus of claim 1, wherein said DNA polynucleotide encoding said virus is at least 99% identical, at a full length nucleotide level, to SEQ ID NO:67. 5. The virus of claim 1, wherein said DNA polynucleotide encoding said virus is at least 99.5% identical, at a full length nucleotide level, to SEQ ID NO:67. 6. The virus of claim 1 wherein the modification of ORF3 comprises a deletion that results in amino acids LTANPL at positions 138-143 (immediately after NGKAA in SEQ ID NO:48) and truncation of the ORE protein after position 143. 7. The virus of claim 1 wherein conservative substitutions for one or more of the designated amino acids are selected from: (1) valine or isoleucine for leucine; (2) glycine for proline; and (3) lysine or arginine for histidine. 8. A vaccine composition comprising a porcine epidemic diarrhea virus (PEDV) according to claim 1, and a carrier, wherein said composition is capable of protecting swine from challenge by both variant and prototype strains of PEDV and preventing or treating one or more symptoms associated with PEDV infection, and wherein achievement of protection is determined by an endpoint selected from the group consisting of prevention or control of any of the PEDV infection symptoms of dehydration, fever, diarrhea, vomiting, poor lactational performance, poor reproduction performance, mortality, and prevention or control of weight loss or failure to gain weight. 9. The vaccine composition of claim 8 wherein the virus is live or killed. 10. The vaccine composition of claim 8 wherein said carrier is a diluent. 11. The vaccine composition of claim 9 further comprising an adjuvant. 12. The vaccine composition of claim 8 wherein said protected swine include any of sows, gilts, boars, hogs, and piglets. 13. The vaccine composition of claim 12 wherein said vaccine is effective in a single dose program. 14. The vaccine composition of claim 12 wherein said vaccine is effective in a two dose program. 15. The vaccine composition of claim 14, wherein the first dose is administered when the piglet is about 1-7 days old, and the second dose is administered when the piglet is 2-5 weeks old. 16. The vaccine composition of claim 13, wherein the single dose is administered at about 1-21 days old, preferably at about 1-7 days old. 17. The vaccine composition of any of claim 8, wherein the minimum effective dose is between about 10 and about 106 logl0TCID50. 18. The vaccine composition of claim 11 wherein the adjuvant is de-oiled lecithin dissolved in an oil, usually light liquid paraffin and aluminum hydroxide. 19. The vaccine composition of claim 11, wherein said adjuvant is CpG/DEAE- dextran/mineral oil (TXO). 20. An isolated Porcine Epidemic Diarrhea Virus (PEDV) that is encoded by a nucleotide sequence that is at least 90%, 95%, 96%, 97%, 98% or 99% identical, at a full length nucleotide level, to SEQ ID: NO:37, wherein said nucleotide sequence comprises one of both of (1) an ORFla/lb protein having a proline residue at the amino acid position thereof corresponding to position 551 (immediately after DAT) in SEQ ID NO:46; and (2) a spike protein having a histidine residue at the amino acid position thereof corresponding to position 973 (immediately after PFS) in SEQ ID NO: 47. 21. A method of treating or preventing disease in a piglet caused by PEDV, comprising administering to said piglet a first dose of the vaccine composition of claim 8 when said piglet is about 1-7 days old. 22. The method of claim 21 wherein said administering further includes administering a second dose of said vaccine when the piglet is about 2-5 weeks old. 23. The method of claim 22, wherein 2 doses are administered to the piglet, and the parent sow, although vaccinated pre-breeding, was not vaccinated pre-farrowing. 24. The method of claim 22, wherein 2 doses are administered to the piglet, and the parent sow is vaccinated pre-farrowing. 26. A method of treating or preventing disease in a piglet caused by PEDV, comprising administering to said piglet a single effective dose of the vaccine composition of claim 8 

